<span id="freeTextContainer16128318794335396870">Another well written book by John Grisham that flows easily and keeps the reader wanting to read more.<br/>The book is full of interesting if not nasty characters that are described perfectly by John Grisham. There are a number of sub plots that bring interest and intrigue into the novel. The first 100+ pages were very good but unfortunately the book did lose its way a little after that otherwise I would have rated it even higher.</span>

          </span>
